{"schema_version":"1","crate":"texts","version":"0.1.0","id":"a4b992ab42964e5b","name":"Texts","qualified_name":"Texts","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"src/texts.ads","line":5,"column":9},"code":"package Texts","documentation":{"description":"A minimalistic library to deal with human texts while providing\nthe basic functionality of a string type. Biased towards Alire\nneeds, so features will be haphazard. The main goal is to make\nWide_Wide_Unbounded_String a bit more comfortable, while remaining\ncompatible with Ada 2012, and also staying safely within Unicode.\n\nMuch more powerful libraries exist (e.g., vss, uxstrings), but they\neither require Ada 2022, a compiler newer than those used to build\nAlire, or bring in too much extra baggage. It is conceivable that as\nAlire leaves behind those restrictions with time, this library just\nacts as a wrapper over those fancier alternatives."},"simple_types":[{"id":"ce98b646818bb0fd","name":"Encodings","qualified_name":"Texts.Encodings","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"src/texts.ads","line":19,"column":9},"code":"type Encodings is\n  (Latin_1,\n   UTF_8\n  );","documentation":{"enumeration_literals":[{"name":"Latin_1","description":"The native encoding of Ada strings. In conformant mode, or for\nAlire projects with default settings, String literals will have this\nencoding (not UTF-8, even if the source files are UTF-8-encoded!).\nNOTE that strings read with Ada.Text_IO will be also Latin-1-encoded."},{"name":"UTF_8","description":""}]}}],"tagged_types":[{"id":"1e0875114b41ba23","name":"Text","qualified_name":"Texts.Text","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"src/texts.ads","line":32,"column":9},"code":"type Text is tagged private;","documentation":{"description":"A Unicode text. Internal representation is deliberately private."},"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"Texts.\"<\"","id":"54c3f51a0bdbc2c4","unit":"texts"},{"qualified_name":"Texts.\"=\"","id":"f1726f6efc04f474","unit":"texts"